text:
350 Fifth Avenue, (Empire State Building), west side from W. 34th to 33rd Streets, (general view westward).

A westward view from the above location towards the North (Hudson) River and its Jersey shore. In the center are, the Pennsylvania Station, the main U. S. Post Office and the New York Central Tracks and yard. To the right is W. 34th Street, with the Nelson Tower at Seventh Avenue, and the Hotel New Yorker at Eighth Avenue.

September 24, 1931

P. L. Sperr
